Equally valid is a comment by Yarows that: β€�As a parent, wouldnβ€™t you rather pay $88 once for your high school student to receive effective screening for potential cardiovascular sudden death rather than yearly ineffective and unproven sports physicals. This cost is less than that of a pair of athletic shoesβ€� (referring to the American screening system).38
